ons of everyday life guide her readers through the stages of her cultural apprenticeship. In the end, as Bjork joins the circle dance, she is a stranger to the community still, but a familiar and welcome one.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aTharu (South Asian people)zTarai Region (India and Nepal)xSocial life and customs. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies.  aAmerican Ethnologist.  aHimalayan Research.  aanthropologist as author.  aanthropology autobiography.  aanthropology.  aasian studies.  acultural travel narratives.  acustoms in nepal.  amemoir nepal.  anepal.  anepalese culture.  anepalese customs.  anepalese studies.  anepali anthropology.  anepali culture.  anepali customs.  anepali ethnography.  anepali history.  anepali studies.  apipariya.  asocial life in nepal.  asouth asian studies.  astudies in nepali history and society.  astudies of nepali society.  atarai region of nepal.  atharu people.  atharu.  atravel writing nepal.  atravel writing south asia.  atravel writing.  atravelogue nepal.  atravelogue south asia.  awomen writing culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172531940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725319423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725319/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles